I‚Äôve missed you!!! Yes YOU! The one actually reading this right now!! I know how these social media feeds work... you flip through, like what you like & keep moving... but for you actually giving me a few moments of your day I want to say, hi! And thank you. üôèüèª
I began writing as a small girl, mostly poetry but more like Hallmark, not Hemingway. I loved alliteration and making words rhyme. I didn‚Äôt truly embrace this gift until 4 years ago when I began writing after a deep loss in my life.  I found writing to become my therapy, my comfort, my outlet to get all these words out of my head and onto paper.  This turned into a blog, which is now mostly instagram posts.  I try to stay short & sweet but intentional. When I have a lot to say, which I still do, I‚Äôll write in my blog but most days, a few minutes is all I have to write a few thoughts on my feed.
So tonight I share a short message...

You will survive this.
Everything is going to be ok.
This is not the end & this is not all there is.

Whether you find your hope in a Heavenly Father or humanity, I promise you, you are not alone. I know we are sick of the ‚Äúwe are in this together‚Äù speeches, but we are. I‚Äôm tired of this too. My social side just wants to visit, laugh & play (without a mask!), while my introverted side wants to hold on to these sacred rhythms of slowing down. But friends, as the horrific months following 9/11 or Hurricane Harvey healed with time, so will this. Let‚Äôs embrace what is good & let go of what is not. Unhealthy relationships, overworking, self hate, fear, anger & angst. 

We ARE in this together but we must speak up. We must share our story. We must come out of hiding.
These past 2 months have emotionally turned me up, down, left & right... but I see a bigger picture, I see a brighter plan. 
So if you are still with me, still reading, thank you üôèüèª thank you for allowing me to hug you with my words & embrace you with my encouragement. 
If you feel like you have nobody in this world, you have me. I see you and I‚Äôm fighting for you. YOU (yes you) are in my prayers. God brought you this far & He won‚Äôt abandon you now. 

Xoxo,
Your sister 

